title: Are you your decisions or your feelings?
pid: 48478539-10c0-4b70-8c18-aa5ba22b7232
body: |2-
  Obviously you're both, but identifying more with the feelings
  seems healthier than identifying more with the decisions.
  Defining oneself in terms of one's past decisions
  seems likely to make one resistant to change.
  Recognizing/remembering the feelings that led to those decisions
  seems more likely to facilitate learning, flexibility and self-forgiveness.
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
